    "This difference may arise because instruct models are already pre-trained on instruction formats, making it easier to adapt to new instructions.",
    "Non-instruct models, however, must learn both the instruction format and task, which could explain their smaller decrease in test accuracy.",
    "Overall, 4/6 times, instruct models are more vulnerable to REGTEXT, underscoring the effectiveness of REGTEXT on pretrained and instruction-tuned models alike.",
